==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marinade
<hw>Mar`i*nade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.: cf. It.
<ets>marinato</ets> marinade, F. <ets>mariner</ets> to preserve food for
use at sea. See <er>Marinate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A
brine or pickle containing wine or vinegar, with oil, herbs, and spices,
for enriching the flavor of meat and fish, which are steeped in it prior
to cooking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>marinara</ent>⟦br⟧
